I grew so thirsty at night,

34:44.498 --> 34:48.960
she brought me a glass of water every
night and laid her hand upon my brow.

34:49.045 --> 34:52.172
She was... so tender.

34:52.965 --> 34:56.927
When my father was away
I slept in her bed.

34:57.011 --> 35:03.767
One afternoon, the wife of the
Canadian ambassador was invited to tea.

35:03.851 --> 35:07.395
She brought her daughter Caroline.

35:07.480 --> 35:13.068
When my mother showed her mother our
garden we were left alone, the children.

35:13.152 --> 35:18.990
Suddenly Eva said "Miss Caroline,
do you sleep with your mother?"

35:22.328 --> 35:24.454
Caroline said "No. Do you?"

35:24.539 --> 35:28.500
And Eva said "He does."

35:29.836 --> 35:34.256
And all my sisters giggled, and Caroline
looked at me and smiled and said:

35:34.340 --> 35:37.676
"I think that's really awfully sweet."

35:37.760 --> 35:40.262
And she became my wife.

35:45.852 --> 35:52.566
Not at that moment, of course. We were
both only... 11 years old at the time.

36:06.497 --> 36:08.999
Where on earth are we?

36:11.085 --> 36:13.170
Do you know?

36:13.671 --> 36:16.590
Let me sit down. I've got such a...

36:17.675 --> 36:20.260
I've got such a headache.

36:22.305 --> 36:24.764
Can you press the back of my neck?

36:24.849 --> 36:26.933
Just there.

36:28.895 --> 36:31.897
- Oh, God. I'm going to...
- What?

36:34.150 --> 36:36.234
(retches)

36:41.199 --> 36:43.283
(Coughs)

36:47.330 --> 36:49.456
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

36:50.374 --> 36:53.877
I'm all right. I just have to sit down.

36:53.961 --> 36:56.213
I can't walk any more.

36:58.466 --> 37:00.550
Hold me.

37:06.140 --> 37:08.850
What a terrible man.

37:08.935 --> 37:11.019
Who was he?

37:17.360 --> 37:19.694
We're on holiday.

37:54.355 --> 37:56.439
(schoolgirls chant)

38:30.933 --> 38:32.809
[Wary-

38:33.853 --> 38:35.937
Wake up.

38:38.024 --> 38:41.985
- Where are we?
- I don't know. Venice. Come on.

38:43.362 --> 38:45.447
Come on.

38:47.658 --> 38:49.743
You're a weight.

39:09.555 --> 39:11.639
I've been bitten.

39:11.724 --> 39:14.017
Try not to scratch.

39:15.186 --> 39:17.479
I'm so thirsty.

39:18.773 --> 39:22.984
You're going to have to
look after me today.

39:23.069 --> 39:27.322
- Why? Did you look after me yesterday?
- (laughs)

39:31.577 --> 39:33.661
I'm so thirsty.

39:35.122 --> 39:37.332
(Ship's horn)

39:37.458 --> 39:42.045
There's the waterfront.
Come on. There'll be a cafe.

39:55.726 --> 39:58.186
Let's go in the shade.

39:59.688 --> 40:01.773
(Mary yawns)

40:16.122 --> 40:18.373
We'd like to order something to drink.

40:18.457 --> 40:20.959
I will tell your waiter.

40:40.896 --> 40:43.731
I wonder how the children are.

40:45.526 --> 40:48.069
Well, you spoke to them, when was it?

40:48.154 --> 40:51.573
- Was it yesterday?
- How were they then?

40:52.491 --> 40:54.993
It's like a prison here.

40:56.829 --> 40:58.913
Let's go home.

41:02.126 --> 41:06.880
- The flight's paid for. It's not for five days.
- We could get another one.

41:06.964 --> 41:10.091
Why do you want to go home?
Excuse me!

41:11.886 --> 41:14.053
I can't believe it. He's coming.

41:14.138 --> 41:20.393
Bringing the children with us would have
made all the difference. To me, anyway.

41:24.190 --> 41:26.774
- Signore?
- A jug of water, please. With ice.

41:26.817 --> 41:30.195
- Water?
- Um... coffee.

41:30.279 --> 41:32.906
- Croissant? Eggs? Juice?
- No, just water.

41:32.990 --> 41:37.202
- Let's go to the hotel and get water there.
- All right.

41:37.244 --> 41:40.622
He's probably bringing it anyway.

41:41.415 --> 41:44.167
I don't know why we came here.

41:45.169 --> 41:49.130
We've been here before.
Why did we come again?

41:53.177 --> 41:56.095
Actually, I remember why we came.

41:57.723 --> 42:01.684
We thought we'd find out
what to do, didn't we?

42:02.937 --> 42:05.647
What to do about you and me.

42:08.984 --> 42:10.610
Well?

42:12.613 --> 42:15.114
Have you found out?

42:16.242 --> 42:22.080
I haven't. I just want to go home.
To my own bed and my kids.

42:28.921 --> 42:31.005
Or maybe you have.

42:31.882 --> 42:35.093
Maybe you have decided what you want.

42:36.512 --> 42:38.596
What you want to do.

42:41.809 --> 42:43.893
Have you?

42:50.234 --> 42:51.568
No.

43:03.289 --> 43:07.458
Oh, God. We should have
gone back to the hotel.

43:12.756 --> 43:15.466
He's missed us.

43:32.192 --> 43:34.277
My friends.

43:35.821 --> 43:39.032
- How are you both?
- Terrible. We slept in the street.

43:39.116 --> 43:41.200
Street?

43:41.285 --> 43:44.912
- After we left you...
- We didn't have a map.

43:44.997 --> 43:51.044
I'm horrified. It's entirely my fault. I kept
you late with wine and stupid stories.

43:51.128 --> 43:54.505
- Don't scratch. It's not a question of that.
- It's my fault.

43:54.590 --> 43:59.218
And it's my responsibility to correct it.
You must come to my house.

43:59.303 --> 44:02.430
- Your coffee.
- Senta. Lasci stare.

44:02.514 --> 44:04.599
(Colin) No, we have a hotel.

44:04.683 --> 44:10.396
My house is a thousand times
more comfortable, peaceful, serene.

44:11.357 --> 44:13.524
We take a taxi.

44:14.318 --> 44:15.610
Please.

44:16.695 --> 44:19.405
- What do you think?
- All right.

44:26.372 --> 44:28.456
(laughs) The street!

47:04.071 --> 47:07.782
- Where are we?
- Robert brought us here.

47:10.577 --> 47:13.788
Robert. Where's he?

47:13.872 --> 47:15.957
I don't know.

47:20.170 --> 47:22.255
What time is it?

47:22.339 --> 47:24.006
Evening.

47:25.676 --> 47:29.637
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes, wonderfully.

47:38.313 --> 47:40.857
How's your bite?

47:40.941 --> 47:43.192
It's gone.

47:43.235 --> 47:45.444
Where's my watch?

47:47.322 --> 47:49.490
Where's our clothes?

47:52.286 --> 47:54.579
Have you seen them?

48:07.551 --> 48:09.635
Not in there.

48:25.736 --> 48:27.904
Not in here.

48:27.988 --> 48:29.739
No?

48:32.534 --> 48:35.745
Don't you think we ought to find them?

48:38.123 --> 48:40.791
- I feel good.
- I must find out what's going on.

48:40.876 --> 48:44.295
I just can't walk around here
stark bloody naked.

48:44.379 --> 48:48.841
I think there's a dressing gown
hanging up in there.

48:55.807 --> 48:58.309
I can't wear this. Look.

49:01.647 --> 49:04.815
Yes, you can. You look lovely.

49:05.609 --> 49:07.944
You look like a god.

49:08.946 --> 49:12.365
I think I'm going to have to
take you to bed.

49:12.449 --> 49:18.955
- This isn't a dressing gown, it's a nightie.
- You've no idea how good you feel in it.

49:19.039 --> 49:22.708
I can't walk around a stranger's house
dressed like this.

49:22.793 --> 49:25.086
Not with an erection!

49:30.384 --> 49:32.468
Here. Put it on.

49:33.345 --> 49:35.930
Find out what's going on.

49:50.737 --> 49:52.822
How do I look?

50:09.464 --> 50:11.716
Hello.

50:11.800 --> 50:14.885
I'm Caroline, Robert's wife.

50:14.970 --> 50:18.097
- Well, you're looking rested!
- Hello.

50:18.181 --> 50:20.766
Come outside. It's nice.

50:26.064 --> 50:27.690
- Wow!
- Mm.

50:27.774 --> 50:33.070
It is beautiful, isn't it? I spend
as much time as possible out here.

50:33.155 --> 50:36.574
- I'm Mary Kenway.
- Yes, I know.

50:37.826 --> 50:40.745
- Come and sit down.
- Is this yours?

50:42.039 --> 50:43.956
Yes.

50:44.041 --> 50:45.875
I made it.

50:45.959 --> 50:49.462
I sometimes sit out here
and do embroidery. I like embroidery.

50:49.546 --> 50:51.756
It's lovely.

50:51.840 --> 50:55.801
- Would you like a biscuit? Take one.
- Thanks.

50:56.803 --> 51:01.682
You must be hungry. Robert wants you
to stay for dinner. He'll be back for dinner.

51:01.767 --> 51:06.020
He's gone to his bar.
A new manager starts there tonight.

51:06.104 --> 51:08.898
- His bar?
- Yes.

51:08.982 --> 51:12.818
You were there last night, weren't you?

51:12.944 --> 51:18.157
- He didn't say it was his bar.
- It's a kind of a hobby, I guess.

51:19.076 --> 51:24.080
But you know more about it than I do.
I've never been there.

51:28.627 --> 51:32.046
Have you done something to your back?

51:32.130 --> 51:37.134
It helps to move. Sometimes
I just stand up and move about.

51:39.012 --> 51:42.223
- Are you fond of your friend?
- Colin?

51:44.476 --> 51:49.313
I hope you don't mind.
There's something I must tell you.

51:51.358 --> 51:55.402
While you were both asleep
I came in and looked at you both.

51:55.487 --> 52:01.742
I just sat on the chaise for half an hour.
I just sat there and looked at you both.

52:02.619 --> 52:04.286
Oh.

52:07.415 --> 52:11.669
Colin is very beautiful, isn't he?
Robert said he was.

52:11.753 --> 52:16.966
You are too, of course.
You both have such wonderful skin.

52:20.011 --> 52:21.971
Are you in love?

52:22.055 --> 52:24.140
Well, I...

52:25.142 --> 52:28.519
I do love him. I suppose.

52:28.603 --> 52:31.564
Not quite like when we first met.

52:31.648 --> 52:35.317
I trust him, really.
He's my closest friend.

52:35.402 --> 52:38.320
But what do you mean by "in love"?

52:39.531 --> 52:43.868
I mean that you'd do absolutely
anything for the other person.

52:43.952 --> 52:48.247
And you'd let them do
absolutely anything to you.

52:48.331 --> 52:50.332
Anything?

52:50.834 --> 52:54.044
- If you're in love with somebody, you...
- (door opens)

53:01.386 --> 53:06.348
- Hello!
- Colin, this is Caroline, Robert's wife.

53:06.433 --> 53:09.435
- Are you having a nice time?
- Um...

53:09.519 --> 53:13.272
- On your holiday?
- Yes, except we keep getting lost.

53:13.356 --> 53:15.441
Pull up a chair.

53:18.695 --> 53:20.279
Oh, my God.

53:20.363 --> 53:22.031
What?

53:22.115 --> 53:27.828
Your clothes. I forgot.
I washed and dried them. I clean forgot.

53:27.913 --> 53:29.997
I must tell you where they are.

53:30.081 --> 53:33.209
But before I do you should tell him
what I told you.

53:33.293 --> 53:37.588
- What?
- What I did while you were both asleep.

53:37.672 --> 53:39.965
Oh. Right.

53:41.343 --> 53:45.679
Caroline came in and looked at us
both whilst we were asleep.

53:45.764 --> 53:47.556
Oh, did She?

53:48.934 --> 53:50.601
Yes.

53:51.811 --> 53:56.065
You were so peaceful.
Just like a baby.

53:57.275 --> 54:02.488
- Babies can be very ratty in their sleep.
- Oh, no, not him.

54:02.572 --> 54:07.660
- I'm sure he always sleeps sweetly.
- Yes, but I'm not a baby.

54:07.744 --> 54:12.206
I never said you were.
I only said that you slept like a baby.

54:12.290 --> 54:18.379
Now, listen. Robert is very keen for you
to stay and have dinner with us.

54:18.421 --> 54:22.299
He told me not to let you
have your clothes till you agreed.

54:22.384 --> 54:23.717
(laughter)

54:23.802 --> 54:26.387
You must be starving, anyway.

54:27.389 --> 54:29.431
So you will?

54:30.892 --> 54:34.478
- Well, I...
- Oh, please. If you don't, he'll blame me.

54:34.562 --> 54:37.481
- (Colin) Let's stay.
- Oh, good.

54:40.318 --> 54:43.445
And... now can I have my clothes?

54:44.948 --> 54:49.827
They're locked in your
bathroom cupboard. Here's the key.

54:49.911 --> 54:52.913
- Thanks.
- Just through there.

54:58.169 --> 55:01.839
Isn't it sweet when men are shy?

55:01.923 --> 55:03.882
It's so sweet.

55:03.967 --> 55:06.635
Tell me, what do you do?
Do you work?

55:06.720 --> 55:12.766
Well, I mainly do voice-overs these days.
Commercials.

55:12.851 --> 55:16.562
I was with a women's group
until about six months ago.

55:16.646 --> 55:20.274
- What do you mean, a women's group?
- A theatre group.

55:20.358 --> 55:26.113
You're an actress?
What a beautiful thing that must be.

55:26.197 --> 55:29.783
Well, sometimes.
Anyway, the group broke up, so...

55:29.868 --> 55:33.120
Women. It was all women?

55:33.872 --> 55:40.294
Some of us wanted to bring in men and
the rest of them wanted to keep it pure.

55:40.378 --> 55:42.463
That's what broke us up.

55:42.547 --> 55:48.260
How can you do a play with only women?
I mean, what could happen?

55:48.345 --> 55:51.972
Happen? Well, you...

55:52.057 --> 55:56.143
You could have a play about
two women who have only just met

55:56.227 --> 56:00.064
sitting on a balcony talking.

56:00.148 --> 56:04.151
- But they'd probably be waiting for a man.
- (laughs)

56:04.235 --> 56:09.031
And then he'd come.
And then something would happen.

56:13.661 --> 56:15.746
(gasp of pain)

56:18.291 --> 56:21.335
- It hurts when I laugh.
- Can I do anything?

56:21.419 --> 56:24.546
Would you touch me here on my neck?

56:24.589 --> 56:27.132
There. Press it.

56:27.217 --> 56:29.468
No, harder.

56:29.552 --> 56:32.388
Yeah. That's it, thank you.

56:38.812 --> 56:42.815
- We did an all-women Hamlet once.
- Hamlet?

56:43.149 --> 56:49.029
I've never read that play. In fact, I haven't
seen a play since I was at school.

56:49.114 --> 56:55.369
Isn't that the one with the ghost,
and then everybody dies at the end?

56:55.453 --> 56:58.330
- Were you the star?
- No.

56:58.415 --> 57:00.499
- Hello.
- Hello.

57:01.459 --> 57:04.670
- Have you slept well?
- Wonderfully.

57:04.754 --> 57:07.464
- What an apartment.
- I'll get the glasses.

57:07.549 --> 57:10.259
It belonged to my grandfather.

57:11.469 --> 57:13.554
You see that island?

57:14.222 --> 57:20.477
That's Cemetery Island. My grandfather
and my father are both buried there.

57:22.814 --> 57:27.693
- You're staying for dinner, I trust?
- I'll get dressed.

57:28.695 --> 57:31.280
A glass of champagne first.

57:36.786 --> 57:38.662
Carolina!

57:56.639 --> 57:58.724
Thank you.

57:59.976 --> 58:02.478
You look like an angel.

58:05.732 --> 58:07.983
How are you feeling?

58:08.067 --> 58:09.568
Better.

58:09.652 --> 58:11.737
To Colin and Mary.

58:15.992 --> 58:18.994
- Dinner.
- I'd better get dressed.

58:29.714 --> 58:31.798
Thank you.

58:46.564 --> 58:48.732
Beautiful place.

59:02.413 --> 59:06.083
These books are the favourite
literature of my father.

59:06.167 --> 59:08.293
And my grandfather.

59:08.378 --> 59:10.462
All first editions.

59:13.299 --> 59:17.970
These are things my father
used every day. Small things.

59:18.930 --> 59:25.310
- He used opera glasses every day?
- No. He used opera glasses at the opera.

59:27.355 --> 59:30.274
They belonged to my grandfather.

59:31.359 --> 59:36.697
Your father seems to be...
very important to you.

59:36.781 --> 59:40.909
My father and his father
understood themselves clearly.

59:40.994 --> 59:44.955
They were men
and they were proud of their sex.

59:45.039 --> 59:47.165
Women understood them too.

59:47.250 --> 59:51.837
Now women treat men like children
because they can't take them seriously,

59:51.921 --> 59:57.301
but men like my father and grandfather
women took very seriously.

59:57.385 --> 01:00:01.555
There was no uncertainty.
No confusion.

01:00:05.643 --> 01:00:07.311
So.

01:00:11.190 --> 01:00:16.361
This is a museum.
Dedicated to the good old days, hm?

01:00:55.068 --> 01:00:57.152
(faint conversation)

01:01:03.993 --> 01:01:07.621
So, how is England?
Lovely, dear old England?

01:01:07.705 --> 01:01:11.208
Hampshire, Wiltshire,
Cumberland, Yorkshire?

01:01:11.292 --> 01:01:12.876
Harrods?

01:01:13.419 --> 01:01:17.047
Such a beautiful country.
Such beautiful traditions.

01:01:17.131 --> 01:01:21.593
Well, it's not quite so beautiful now.
Is it, Colin?

01:01:22.178 --> 01:01:25.430
- Colin, are you feeling all right?
- Mm.

01:01:25.515 --> 01:01:28.850
In what way?
In what way not beautiful?

01:01:29.852 --> 01:01:31.728
Oh...

01:01:31.813 --> 01:01:33.397
I don't know.

01:01:33.481 --> 01:01:36.024
Freedom. You know?

01:01:36.109 --> 01:01:40.237
Freedom? What kind of freedom?
Freedom to do what?

01:01:41.030 --> 01:01:44.574
- Freedom to be free.
- You want to be free?

01:01:46.911 --> 01:01:49.830
- Free to do what?
- You don't believe in it?

01:01:49.914 --> 01:01:55.085
Sure I believe in it, but sometimes
a few rules, you know, not a bad thing.

01:01:55.128 --> 01:02:02.008
First, society has to be protected
from perverts. Everybody knows that.

01:02:02.093 --> 01:02:08.014
My position is simple. Put them all
up against the wall and shoot them.

01:02:08.099 --> 01:02:11.101
What society needs to do is purify itself.

01:02:11.185 --> 01:02:14.438
The English government's
going in the right direction.

01:02:14.522 --> 01:02:17.774
We could learn a lot of lessons from them.

01:02:17.859 --> 01:02:23.238
I'm an Englishman, and I have to say I
disagree violently with what you just said.

01:02:23.281 --> 01:02:25.449
I think it's Shit.

01:02:28.369 --> 01:02:34.082
I respect you as an English man.
But not if you're a communist poof.

01:02:36.210 --> 01:02:39.337
You're not a poof, are you?

01:02:39.422 --> 01:02:42.549
It's the right word, no? Or is it fruit?

01:02:45.511 --> 01:02:48.680
Talking about fruit, it's time for coffee.

01:02:48.765 --> 01:02:52.184
- No, I think we should be going.
- Yes, we must.

01:02:52.268 --> 01:02:55.812
- But coffee!
- No, we've stayed far too long already.

01:02:55.897 --> 01:02:59.149
- But thank you so much.
- You're tired.

01:02:59.233 --> 01:03:00.859
Thank you.

01:03:00.943 --> 01:03:05.947
Our hotel won't seem quite the same
after your apartment.

01:03:16.959 --> 01:03:19.127
Oh.

01:03:19.212 --> 01:03:20.962
Nice.

01:03:21.047 --> 01:03:23.548
I'm a keen amateur photographer.

01:03:23.633 --> 01:03:27.135
- So we go straight on till we get to the...
- Take the bridge.

01:03:27.220 --> 01:03:31.640
Please. Please come back.
Please. It's important.

01:03:31.724 --> 01:03:33.892
(whispers) I can't get out.

01:03:33.976 --> 01:03:37.646
- Love to.
- It's my back. The stairs.

01:03:39.065 --> 01:03:44.152
Anyway, thank you so much
for your kindness. Good night.

01:03:46.447 --> 01:03:50.492
- It's meant a great deal to us.
- Good night.

01:04:13.432 --> 01:04:19.563
You know, when I saw you on that
terrace tonight, in that nightdress...

01:04:26.529 --> 01:04:28.905
you looked so beautiful...

01:04:31.200 --> 01:04:34.119
my heart... jumped.

01:04:35.621 --> 01:04:40.625
But I told you how you looked
in that nightdress, didn't I?

01:05:08.195 --> 01:05:11.531
- (maid knocks) Permesso.
- (Colin) oh, please!

01:05:11.616 --> 01:05:15.785
- Dovrei pulire la stanza.
- (Colin) We're on our bloody holiday.

01:05:20.082 --> 01:05:23.335
(Mary) Come here. Come here.

01:05:39.810 --> 01:05:41.895
What's it like?

01:05:43.356 --> 01:05:46.608
I often wonder what it feels like.

01:05:46.734 --> 01:05:48.818
What's what like?

01:05:48.903 --> 01:05:54.908
What's it feel like to be the girl?
I mean the feeling of being...

01:06:00.373 --> 01:06:02.832
It feels...

01:06:02.917 --> 01:06:04.793
like...

01:06:05.753 --> 01:06:07.420
this.

01:06:32.071 --> 01:06:34.447
(Mary) I'm crazy about you.

01:06:38.744 --> 01:06:41.287
(Colin) I'm crazy about you.

01:07:01.058 --> 01:07:03.560
Don't open the shutters.

01:07:03.644 --> 01:07:05.562
Come here.

01:07:05.771 --> 01:07:07.856
Come here.

01:07:08.649 --> 01:07:10.734
Sit down.

01:07:14.363 --> 01:07:15.572
Ow!

01:07:15.656 --> 01:07:17.699
